docs/working/REVIEW_FINDINGS.md:2540:Reviewed slices / commits since the prior architecture review:
docs/working/REVIEW_FINDINGS.md:2559:During this architecture-review run, `scripts/ralph-validate.sh` looked for `.ralph/venv/bin/python` inside the active worktree, did not find it, and fell back to bare `python3`. That violates the run prompt's backend-interpreter rule and failed with an architecture-mismatched `_cffi_backend` import. Manual backend gates passed when run with the required repo-level interpreter `/Users/amitkallapa/Loan Management System Development/.ralph/venv/bin/python`.
